    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Analysing 92,598 variant screening tests performed on SARS-CoV-2 positive samples collected in France between 1 July and 31 August 2021 shows an increase of Kappa-like infections. Full genome sequencing reveals that these correspond to Delta variants bearing the S:E484Q mutation. Most of these sequences belong to a phylogenetic cluster and also bear the S:T95I mutation. Further monitoring is needed to determine if this trend is driven by undocumented superspreading events or an early signal of future viral evolutionary dynamics.</jats:p>",
